<subSubSection id="24C62EECFEFC579935E7619049595B2B" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" type="taxon discussion">
<paragraph id="4C076D923103005ACDC4C1F9A1B42568" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Taxon discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EEFDD22E12942C48E6182018422C3133" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">This is a new addition to the Greek flora. Previous old reports are considered erroneous.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A1FF5E0ACBF37FE24E9B3DA314E64098" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">
The 
<taxonomicName id="47B30B2BF708A83A4EB11F0F9259B1DB" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Aster" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Aster amellus" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="amellus">
<emphasis id="3D4B2CEE03175146F8B1C60CA8A7EBFA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Aster amellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
records in Greece have a long history. Old reports from the dry habitats of Attiki near Athens under either 
<taxonomicName id="E725B6A6AD9A26EB6EA874AB0182CEAA" genus="A." lsidName="A. amellus" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" rank="species" species="amellus">
<emphasis id="7CE793D5F9E3374D663188EC5EF9DC99" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">A. amellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as in 
<bibRefCitation id="C2E9B2C2401F8E661DAD2CB9DA3FDF42" author="Boissier, E." journalOrPublisher="H. George, Genevae et Basileae, Lugduni" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7667877" refString="Boissier, E., 1875. Flora Orientalis sive enumeratio plantarum in oriente a Graecia et Aegypto ad Indiae fines hucusque observatarum 3. H. George, Genevae et Basileae, Lugduni" title="Flora Orientalis sive enumeratio plantarum in oriente a Graecia et Aegypto ad Indiae fines hucusque observatarum 3" year="1875">Boissier (1875)</bibRefCitation>
(
<emphasis id="EDD41C42315B46248E5D58847032B33E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">hab. in collibus apricis Atticae</emphasis>
) or 
<taxonomicName id="8E1F14F2053B46D8602789A53659E387" genus="A." lsidName="A. atticus" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" rank="species" species="atticus">
<emphasis id="624C2B91B8C5A34EF452BCF75346ED79" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">A. atticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Pall. (
<bibRefCitation id="AAEF9B7BEBC929BE654982DE74B74BB0" author="Tournefort, J. P." journalOrPublisher="Typographia Regia, Parisiis" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7670103" refString="Tournefort, J. P., 1700. Institutiones rei herbariae, Tomus Primus. Typographia Regia, Parisiis" title="Institutiones rei herbariae, Tomus Primus" year="1700">Tournefort 1700</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="DB1A8B6D78305E56F671459D3637D5E4" author="Jacquin, N. J." journalOrPublisher="Josephi Michaelis Gerold, Aulae Imperialis Typographi, Viennae" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7668817" refString="Jacquin, N. J., 1778. Florae Austriacae Vol. V. Josephi Michaelis Gerold, Aulae Imperialis Typographi, Viennae" title="Florae Austriacae Vol. V" year="1778">Jacquin 1778</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="F639546C9C854EE028AC567AB0843B79" author="Sibthorp, J." journalOrPublisher="Richardii Taylor et Socii, Londini" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7669305" refString="Sibthorp, J., Smith, J. E., 1813. Florae Graecae Prodromus Vol. 2. Richardii Taylor et Socii, Londini" title="Florae Graecae Prodromus Vol. 2" year="1813">Sibthorp and Smith 1813</bibRefCitation>
) were soon disputed. 
<bibRefCitation id="266C3505374FF532100C783A77AEB4C8" author="Halacsy, E." journalOrPublisher="Sumptibus Guilelmi Engelmann, Lipsiae" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7668210" refString="Halacsy, E., 1902. Conspectus Florae Graecae Vol. 2. Sumptibus Guilelmi Engelmann, Lipsiae" title="Conspectus Florae Graecae Vol. 2" year="1902">
<normalizedToken id="0F223911A6657F98C80F67F0B8860F9D" originalValue="Halácsy">Halacsy</normalizedToken>
(1902)
</bibRefCitation>
noted that these old records were probably erroneous; his opinion is followed in the contemporary literature (see 
<bibRefCitation id="3698067DC5EBA39749981DF6647CB206" author="Dimopoulos, P." journalOrPublisher="Botanischer Garten und Botanisches Museum Berlin-Dahlem, Berlin; Hellenic Botanical Society, Athens" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7668013" refString="Dimopoulos, P., Raus, T., Bergmeier, E., Constantinidis, T., Iatrou, G., Kokkini, S., Strid, A., D.Tzanoudakis, , 2013. Vascular plants of Greece: An annotated checklist. Botanischer Garten und Botanisches Museum Berlin-Dahlem, Berlin; Hellenic Botanical Society, Athens" title="Vascular plants of Greece: An annotated checklist" year="2013">Dimopoulos et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="929D30FB306FFB4FA392D55AFC30B112" author="Fraas, C." journalOrPublisher="EA Fleischmann, Muenchen" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7668135" refString="Fraas, C., 1845. Synopsis plantarum florae classicae. EA Fleischmann, Muenchen" title="Synopsis plantarum florae classicae" year="1845">Fraas (1845)</bibRefCitation>
, however, referred to 
<taxonomicName id="692343D33B4488D5C3365CCC3A82E10D" genus="A." lsidName="A. amellus" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" rank="species" species="amellus">
<emphasis id="E2771FE778351654868A77D50E4B52AA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">A. amellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a plant of salt marshes and coastal swamps from the area of Faliro, south-west of the Athens centre and used the common name &quot; 
<emphasis id="AB9FCAB771A6C6F281FE4FFEEA17FE61" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">valtokratis</emphasis>
&quot; (from the Greek words 
<emphasis id="FDD7C066F7AF8B10CFE50E9D70F02D66" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">
<normalizedToken id="6B9AA10A7F0EE98CAE4275EB7914A313" originalValue="βάλτος">βάλτος</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
, i.e. marsh and 
<emphasis id="06B06A16E8F28B3754696CCE50ECD915" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">
<normalizedToken id="E7ABE02FB366FE9CD4C404D540409721" originalValue="κράτος">κράτος</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
, i.e. power, strength) to identify it. Such a habitat is alien to 
<taxonomicName id="FB3E0FF7BB6C6DF142C9D50EF34D5FA3" genus="A." lsidName="A. amellus" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" rank="species" species="amellus">
<emphasis id="8C78155F5757B9E20E60D00D4836B5C0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">A. amellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a species of drier localities that colonises grasslands, slopes, waysides, scrub formations and wood margins and clearings (
<bibRefCitation id="EE19C4AA9170E4538EE7DA4AB4073796" author="Merxmueller, H." journalOrPublisher="Cambridge University Press, Cambridge" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7668949" refString="Merxmueller, H., Schreiber, A., 1976. Flora Europaea Vol. 4. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge" title="Flora Europaea Vol. 4" year="1976">
<normalizedToken id="D0D9BD3FCB20AB4F710205B7E28A50E4" originalValue="Merxmüller">Merxmueller</normalizedToken>
and Schreiber 1976
</bibRefCitation>
). It is quite safe to assume that 
<bibRefCitation id="6A2E3CFB45AAF276D76729F24CC6C1EF" author="Fraas, C." journalOrPublisher="EA Fleischmann, Muenchen" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7668135" refString="Fraas, C., 1845. Synopsis plantarum florae classicae. EA Fleischmann, Muenchen" title="Synopsis plantarum florae classicae" year="1845">Fraas (1845)</bibRefCitation>
, when mentioning 
<taxonomicName id="9B6D31695EDC1B52609F82609C7C0B27" genus="A." lsidName="A. amellus" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" rank="species" species="amellus">
<emphasis id="40E6260C0519836E31CAF8C20AD08D1D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">A. amellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, was actually referring to 
<taxonomicName id="E5FF36A400E160AEA0FA6355E4493C3A" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Tripolium" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Tripolium pannonicum" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pannonicum">
<emphasis id="B2DC707126D37034F79FAC6FC9B47925" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Tripolium pannonicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Jacq.) Dobrocz. (
<taxonomicName id="572ACC9B5CC94DBA835A3B1A028DFF02" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Aster" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Aster tripolium" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tripolium">
<emphasis id="4F24CF92523DA744B79B79A31B1D184B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Aster tripolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L.), a plant known for its preference for marshes and brackish waters and still found in Attiki. Due to lack of any further evidence during the last 150 years, 
<taxonomicName id="D184EF0C272D9A0D868E56819739FB9A" genus="A." lsidName="A. amellus" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" rank="species" species="amellus">
<emphasis id="A59D784BB215AFC34D0F694E60E594C2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">A. amellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was justifiably excluded from the Greek flora.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2D156DC32E1DF40DF77493651EDE02E8" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">
Our collection of 
<taxonomicName id="E3C8DBB3651853323B0E1F515F6E3429" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Aster" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Aster amellus" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="amellus">
<emphasis id="5001EE2F5431E42E193EB83BBE40BCE9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Aster amellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Rodopi area (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="4A4BD19D71276793B162806521568C3D" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F7677555" captionText="Figure 5. Aster amellus from Mt. Rodopi (photo: P. Doumas)." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e81817.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/640524" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">5</figureCitation>
) is the first that confirms this species as an indigenous member of the Greek flora. Its collection locality lies at a linear distance of ca. 8.5 km south of the Greek-Bulgarian border. According to the distribution map provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="4F0E912800A12CC8B7B5D1B1D8C14973" author="Muenzbergova, Z." journalOrPublisher="Perspectives in Plant Ecology, Evolution and Systematics" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" pagination="151 - 162" refId="B7669042" refString="Muenzbergova, Z., Raabova, J., Castro, S., Pankova, H., 2011. Biological flora of Central Europe: Aster amellus L. (Asteraceae). Perspectives in Plant Ecology, Evolution and Systematics 13 (2): 151 - 162" title="Biological flora of Central Europe: Aster amellus L. (Asteraceae)" volume="13" year="2011">
<normalizedToken id="D02F88ADBB102D7E431ABAB067DE7F97" originalValue="Münzbergová">Muenzbergova</normalizedToken>
et al. (2011)
</bibRefCitation>
, the Greek locality is marginally outside the total distribution range of the species. It is implied that 
<taxonomicName id="D6737DE0804EC309D1ECA091FA8DCBC3" genus="A." lsidName="A. amellus" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" rank="species" species="amellus">
<emphasis id="F3302561E1B1E2B626E3A7712E89AF29" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">A. amellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was suspiciously absent from the Greek territory. From a morphological point of view, the species is polymorphic and includes three different cytotypes: diploids (2n=2x=18), tetraploids (2n=4x=36) and hexaploids (2n=6x=54). Certain literature sources and taxonomic databases recognise subspecific entities that are mostly based on the treatment of 
<bibRefCitation id="A1937D1C00955E0197C850B100F2B4DB" author="Tamamshyan, S. G." journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7670054" refString="Tamamshyan, S. G., 1959. Flora of the USSR, Vol. XXV. Compositae." title="Flora of the USSR, Vol. XXV. Compositae" year="1959">Tamamshyan (1959)</bibRefCitation>
. The Greek samples are pubescent on stems and mostly have scabrid leaves, bear numerous small capitula 9-11 mm wide (ligules excluded), with green, subacute and ciliate involucral bracts often pubescent dorsally. They come closer to subsp. 
<taxonomicName id="725D4C2D1E9E6A2F377BCA4DD64F6846" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Aster" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Aster amellus subsp. bessarabicus" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="amellus" subSpecies="bessarabicus">Aster amellus bessarabicus</taxonomicName>
(Rchb.) 
<normalizedToken id="96048D3936153FE3A0448EE158CD46C0" originalValue="Soó">Soo</normalizedToken>
, but the whole group needs further investigation.
</paragraph>
